is a price taker in the
world market for sugar.

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:09.760
Some of the sugar consumed in Loriland

00:00:09.760 --> 00:00:12.690
is produced domestically
while the rest is imported.

00:00:12.690 --> 00:00:15.320
The world price of sugar is $2 per pound.

00:00:15.320 --> 00:00:18.370
The graph below shows
Loriland's sugar market,

00:00:18.370 --> 00:00:21.780
and P sub W represents the world price.

00:00:21.780 --> 00:00:23.790
So we see our domestic demand,

00:00:23.790 --> 00:00:25.580
we see our domestic supply,

00:00:25.580 --> 00:00:27.670
and then we see the world price.

00:00:27.670 --> 00:00:30.100
All right, now let's try
to answer the questions

00:00:30.100 --> 00:00:32.563
that they have given us.

00:00:33.560 --> 00:00:36.080
At the world price of $2 per pound,

00:00:36.080 --> 00:00:39.230
how much sugar is Loriland importing?

00:00:39.230 --> 00:00:40.150
So pause this video,

00:00:40.150 --> 00:00:42.910
and see if you can figure
that out on your own.

00:00:42.910 --> 00:00:44.870
All right, now let's do it together.

00:00:44.870 --> 00:00:47.960
So at first, you look at
your domestic demand and see,

00:00:47.960 --> 00:00:51.530
well, what would the domestic
demand be at the world price?

00:00:51.530 --> 00:00:54.010
So that would be where
these two lines intersect.

00:00:54.010 --> 00:00:56.070
So the domestic demand at the world price

00:00:56.070 --> 00:00:57.730
