00:00:57.730 --> 00:01:00.030
You might be tempted to
put 14 million pounds here,

00:01:00.030 --> 00:01:01.730
but that would be the
total domestic demand

00:01:01.730 --> 00:01:02.563
at that world price.

00:01:02.563 --> 00:01:04.330
But some of that is domestically produced,

00:01:04.330 --> 00:01:06.460
and some of it is imported.

00:01:06.460 --> 00:01:08.430
How much is domestically produced?

00:01:08.430 --> 00:01:12.250
Well, at a price of $2, the
domestic producers are up

00:01:12.250 --> 00:01:15.830
for producing two million
of those 14 million pounds.

00:01:15.830 --> 00:01:17.650
So this is domestic production.

00:01:17.650 --> 00:01:21.290
And so between these
two points, that length,

00:01:21.290 --> 00:01:24.400
that represents how much
is actually imported.

00:01:24.400 --> 00:01:27.220
So to go from two million
pounds to 14 million pounds,

00:01:27.220 --> 00:01:29.290
14 minus two is 12 million pounds.

00:01:29.290 --> 00:01:30.620
That is imported,

00:01:30.620 --> 00:01:33.570
12 million pounds.

00:01:33.570 --> 00:01:36.150
Part b, suppose that Loriland

00:01:36.150 --> 00:01:38.990
imposes a per-unit
tariff on sugar imports,

00:01:38.990 --> 00:01:42.650
and the new domestic price
including the tariff is $4.

00:01:42.650 --> 00:01:45.820
Identify the new level
of domestic production.

00:01:45.820 --> 00:01:49.160
So once again, pause the video,
and try to figure that out.

00:01:49.160 --> 00:01:51.670
All right, so they say
the new domestic price

00:01:51.670 --> 00:01:53.303
