Well, the domestic consumer
surplus for Loriland

00:02:32.070 --> 00:02:35.290
in this scenario, where this is the price,

00:02:35.290 --> 00:02:38.690
well, then we are going to,
let me scroll down a little bit

00:02:38.690 --> 00:02:41.430
so we can see the entire consumer surplus.

00:02:41.430 --> 00:02:43.800
That is going to be the area

00:02:43.800 --> 00:02:46.310
above this horizontal line at the price

00:02:46.310 --> 00:02:49.610
and below our domestic demand curve.

00:02:49.610 --> 00:02:52.510
So this right over here
is the consumer surplus

00:02:52.510 --> 00:02:54.230
in that scenario.

00:02:54.230 --> 00:02:57.470
And so that is going to be this width,

00:02:57.470 --> 00:03:02.440
which is the quantity demanded,
which is 10 million pounds,

00:03:02.440 --> 00:03:05.110
times the height,

00:03:05.110 --> 00:03:08.280
which is, you're going from four to $9,

